k: & R=\alpha\theta+\frac{\mu}{\lambda_{1}\theta\left(c_{0}\right)^{\sigma}}-\frac{\phi}{\lambda_{1}\left(c_{0}+k\right)^{\sigma}}\\
\mathcal{U}: & \mu^{\prime}=\frac{\lambda_{1}\left(c_{1}^{y}\right)^{\sigma}}{\beta}-\mu\frac{f^{\prime}}{f}-1\\
\mathcal{U}\left(\underline{\theta}\right): & \mu^{\prime}=\frac{\lambda_{1}\left(c_{1}^{y}\right)^{\sigma}}{\beta}-\mu\frac{f^{\prime}}{f}-1-\phi
\end{align*}

\end_inset

The hope is that this introduces sufficient curvature to overcome nonconcavities.
